  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are many important legal precedents in money laundering cases. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. BCCI (1991)\n- Landmark case involving international banking fraud\n- Established stricter regulations on financial institutions\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major international money laundering investigation\n- Resulted in significant regulatory reforms\n\n3. United States v. Santos (2008)\n- Supreme Court case defining money laundering parameters\n- Clarified interpretations of financial criminal statutes\n\n4. Proceeds of Crime Act (UK, 2002)\n- Comprehensive legal framework for money laundering prosecution\n- Expanded definitions and enforcement mechanisms\n\n5. Basel Committee Guidelines\n- International standards for anti-money laundering practices\n- Influential in developing global regulatory approaches\n\nThese cases and guidelines have shaped modern legal understanding of money laundering, establishing important principles for investigation, prosecution, and prevention.\n\nWould you be interested in more detailed information about any of these specific precedents?",
